cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with unsupervised deep learning methods for visual depth and ego-motion estimation tasks, which are primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of recurrent representation across the layers also suggests the involvement of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of generative adversarial nets (GANs) indicates the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE).
